[`SearchPhaseExecutionException#status()`](https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/blob/master/core/src/main/java/org/elasticsearch/action/search/SearchPhaseExecutionException.java#L87-L90) returns a `503 Unavailable` status code if there are no shard failures added to the exception:

```
        if (shardFailures.length == 0) {
            // if no successful shards, it means no active shards, so just return SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE
            return RestStatus.SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE;
        }
```

If an Exception is thrown in the reduce phase (e.g. from the reduce of an aggregation) this means that it will be given a 503 status code since if there were no failures returned from the shards. 

It looks like this is primarily caused by the fact that [`ReduceSearchPhaseException`](https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/blob/master/core/src/main/java/org/elasticsearch/action/search/ReduceSearchPhaseException.java) extends `SearchPhaseExecutionException` so maybe either we should override the `status()` method in `ReduceSearchPhaseException` or we should not have `ReduceSearchPhaseException` extend `SearchPhaseExecutionException`?

